Halve the @Artichoke Hearts{1%jar} lengthwise and pat dry between two layers of #paper towels{}. Halve the @Grape Tomatoes{1%bunch}. Pick the @Parsley{1%bunch} leaves off the stems. Mince or grate the @Garlic{2%cloves}. Peel and dice the @Idaho Potato{12%oz} into 1⁄2–inch pieces.

> Be sure to cut the potatoes as evenly as possible; use the ruler above for help!

Heat a 1/4–inch layer of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add the potatoes and fry for ~{6-7%minutes}, turning to cook on all sides, until golden brown and crispy. Remove from oil and reserve on a #paper-towel lined plate{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the artichokes to the same pan and fry for ~{6-7%minutes}, turning to cook on all sides, until golden brown and crispy. Remove from oil and reserve on a paper-towel lined plate. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Chipotle Dressing ==

Make the chipotle dressing: in a #small bowl{}, mix together the @Mayonnaise{3%tablespoon}, @White Wine Vinegar{1%tablespoon}, garlic (to taste) and @Chipotle Powder{1%teaspoon} (to taste). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Plate the @Arugula{4%oz} and top with tomatoes, @Almonds{1%oz}(sliced), @Goat Cheese{1/4%cup}, potatoes, and artichokes. Drizzle with chipotle dressing, garnish with parsley leaves, and enjoy!